text.tspan: The logo represents the union of the human brain
with a power cable. It brings forward the image of
how humans and the powerful creation by
humans(namely the power cord symbolising
everything thats driven by human invention in the
modern day) co-exists. Codinson, that is about
coding breathes into this concept of creating some
digital wonder using human power of creation.
The logo has the infinity loop as the basic
symbol that connects at the end with the
basic symbol of a code </>. It deals with the
concept that the possibilities of coding are
infinite. With Codinson, people can start
exploring through the infinite possibility at
the grassroot level.
The name Codinson, dwells in the pun of
Odin with Coding. It plays with the word
Odin-son and Coding. Odin was the Norse
God associated with Knowlege and wisdom
among other things. Codinson iterates the
knowledge of coding. This logo is in the
shape of the war helmet of Odin. Also, it is
made with elements of Coding. Made with
‘ / ’, ‘ \ ’, the ‘{ ’ and also the ‘( and )’. These
are inseparable parts of Coding
The horse logo for Codinson deals with the
geometric shapes that constitute the form
of the horse. This logo is a symbol of being
ready to go ahead, a symbol of power and
energy. It says get ready to go on for a
coding adventure trip. It symbolioses the
strength and power that coding gives to
create something new and extraordinary.
This logo shows a zigsaw-puzzle block that
fits into a forward arrow-head. It also has a
<...> sign inside the block representing all
that we can code (within the <>). So, this
logo basically tells that coding might look
like a puzzle that leads to your future(the
arrowhead) prospects. Codinson helps to
solve the puzzle, teach coding so that you
can seamlessly transition into a world of
future coding experience.
Context: CODINSON is an application to learn code, that my group is working on for the group project in our Design1 class.
All the logos here are single-handedly designed by me.
